cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper proposes a new algorithm for Multidimensional Scaling (MDS) on multiple input distance matrices, which involves learning the weights of views (i.e., distance matrices) automatically by exploring the consensus information and complementary nature of views. This task is related to machine learning and data analysis, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Among these sub-categories, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely ones since they are directly related to machine learning and data analysis, while cs.CV is also likely since MDS is often used in computer vision applications. cs.SI and cs.DS are less likely but still possible since they involve data analysis and algorithms.
